name: Top of the Hill Lifestyle. Comfort & Convenience
description:
Experience Seattle's Capitol Hill Lifestyle in this Old World Charm Apartment Home.

A one of a Kind, Fully Furnished, Fully Equipped, Cozy, 1 Bedroom/1 Bath Apartment Home designed for comfortable and convenient living and entertaining with spectacular outdoor dining and lounging spaces where leaving the house can be the day's biggest challenge.

Outstanding Features include the cozy electric fireplace with mood settings, Patio for outdoor dining, cozy reading area, comfortable work space.

License number
STR-OPLI-21-001403
neighborhood_overview:
Capitol Hill is arguably the coolest neighborhood in Seattle! The city's vibrant center of brunch spots, arts, music, parks and boutique galore.

It is young, high-tech and culturally adventurous. It's the epicenter of coffee culture, home to clubs that spawned the grunge movement, and the site of some of Seattle's biggest events, like Block Party and the Pride Parade.

While it's simply home to many, it's also one of the hottest nightlife neighborhoods and has a long list of things to do, from visiting beautiful Volunteer Park to going to the Seattle Asian Art Museum, to dining or hanging out at a microbrewery.

Make your way to Chophouse Row (*1424 11th Ave), where the pedestrian alley and tucked-away courtyard make for a unique indoor/outdoor shopping experience. Local artisans offer everything from corn waffles and cheese blintzes at Marmite to DIY bath bomb kits at Bootyland Kids—and many are making the local retail experience available remotely
host_about:
Born and raised in the Montana, my craze for mountain adventure was ignited by the awe-inspiring Rocky Mountains and led me to Seattle 30 years ago where I have climbed, scaled, scrambled, skied, criss-crossed, trudged, trekked, hiked, biked and kayaked some of the Pacific Northwest’s classic adventures and hidden gems.  

My impetus to see the world began with an obsession to climb in some of the world’s highest mountains. Trudging off to these remote areas to reach enticing peaks, I first discovered the joys of living with the mountain people. This has lead to speaking fluent Spanish, and spending a lot of her time in South America where she I had an adobe apartment in the bohemian district of Lima.

I have had a variety of careers all involving education and the environment:  I was the owner of an outdoor adventure company in Seattle, a program developer and educator, a coordinator for college environmental education, a back country crew leader for restoration and trail work in the North cascades and Alaska, a geologist in the Olympic National Park, wilderness guide in the Pacific Northwest and currently the co-founder and board member of Crooked Trails, a nonprofit international travel company as well as a Property manager and investor in real estate and short term rentals.

I would LOVE to help you create a spectacular, exciting, relaxing stay in Seattle!  I can offer suggestions, itineraries, tours and transport.

name: Seattle City Skyline View w/ King Bed + Parking
description:
This 2022-built modern 3b, 2.5b townhouse is in a quiet neighborhood and perfect for group of friends, couples, families with kids, business travelers. The location is very convenient for visitors to downtown Seattle, UW, Greenlake, tourist attractions and parks. Only 3 blocks away from the Woodland Park Zoo. A free private off-street parking is at the back of the townhouse. It has a large private rooftop deck with panoramic views. Convenient to commercials, restaurants, grocery stores, etc.

The space
This 3B 2.5B brand new townhouse is located in the heart of Fremont. There are 2 bedrooms and 1 full bath on the 1st floor, one of the bedroom has an office desk which allows you to work remotely. 2nd floor is the living room with dining area, kitchen and a powder room. Master bedroom with a private full bath is on the 3rd floor. And a huge roof deck with outdoor chairs and tables so you can have your breakfast while enjoying the views of Seattle city skyline, Mt. R
neighborhood_overview: It is nestled in a quiet residential street but also close to commercial area that you can easily find grocery stores and many restaurants/bars/coffee shops within 5-10 min walk.
host_about:
Hi, this is Leo and Danni, our family has lived in Seattle area for 7 years, we love this city and would like to invite you to take a tour here.

Life is like a box of chocolates, you never know what you're going to get, but a journey to Seattle will guarantee a special memory.

name: Gatsby feel within modern basement 1BR near water
description:
Staycation at this centrally-located spot in Ballard - crown hill neighborhood.
10 mins north of downtown Seattle.
5 minute drive to the locks, or Golden gardens park on the puget sound for paddle boarding, kayaking, or a campfire on the beach.
11 minute walk to Besalu coffee and pastry or Picolono’s for coffee and fresh bread.

The space
Speakeasy Gatsy feel, newly remodeled, well lit basement, brand new warming kitchen that feels like a 1 bedroom apartment. Laundry is available.
Near water, shopping, delicious food and the Sunday 10AM Ballard farmers market off Market street.

Guest access
Front lawn with outside chairs and table. Charcoal BBQ available upon request.

Other things to note
check the QR Code "The Bruno Recs" for places to visit, eat, and activities to do.

One block away from UW Medical Center - Northwest | Seattle Hospital!

Welcome to my 2 bedroom 2 bathroom home nestled in the East Queen Anne neighborhood in downtown Seattle! This unit is perfect for solo travelers, friends, couples, and even those who are in the city for business!

name: Bird's-eye View in Seattle
description:
Be in the heart of it all! Enjoy the best of Seattle with ease & convenience from this stylish condo, just one block from Pike's Place Market!

Paid secure parking spot included in building if needed.

Enjoy city views, easy access to downtown restaurants, shops, and Seattle's famous waterfront. Twenty minute walk to the Space Needle and Seattle Center.

Additional building amenities include exercise facility, hot tub, sauna, pool, a business center, community room, outdoor deck & concierge.

The space
Recently remodeled stylish with one bedroom, a full bath, separate dining room, and top of the line sofa bed in the living room for separate sleeping quarters. New appliances (including washer/dryer) and well stocked kitchen.
Private deck allows you to have your own view of the city skyline, including the famous Smith Tower.

Please note: While there is no AC in the unit, it is an east facing unit, so it will not hea
neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Seattle, one block from Pike's Place Market.

description:
This cozy cottage is short drive to many of Seattle's highlights. Whether it's walking the beach or visiting the vibrant area of capital hill. The cottage is a one room studio house. For air conditioning we only use only an oscillating fan, which is generally plenty sufficient for our climate. Our chickens are fenced in the yard but are easily viewed from the front porch of the cottage. They can be very entertaining. Although, we ask that you not feed them for their safety and well being.

Whether you’re a family looking for budget-friendly finds or a seasoned traveler on the hunt for the latest photo-worthy vista, we have you covered :) We are happy to help provide more information about our neighborhood; just drop us a quick note!
host_about: Hi, my name is Jordan & my partner's name is Travis! We have been living in Seattle, Washington since May 2022! We moved here from Dallas, and love it here! We partner with “Loftium” to create a great experience for our guests! Our passion is traveling, and we try our best to catch a flight a few times a year to explore the world! We are huge cat lovers, I wouldn’t be surprised if we end up with 15 cats later in life!

neighborhood_overview: Wallingford is a neighborhood in north central Seattle, lying on a hill above the north shore of Lake Union about four miles from the downtown core. The neighborhood developed quickly during the early 20th century after the establishment of the University of Washington to the east. With trolley tracks laid through the neighborhood as early as 1907, Wallingford is a classic streetcar suburb, typified by its many 1920s era box houses and bungalows. Commercial development is primarily concentrated along North 45th Street where a number of iconic structures stand including the neon "WALLINGFORD" sign, the Wallingford Center, and the original Dick's Drive-In. With its central location, numerous public amenities, including the world-renowned Gas Works Park, and views of both the Olympic and Cascade mountains, Wallingford has long been home to many middle and upper-class families. neighborhood_overview:
Beacon Hill is a giant, pea pod-shaped neighborhood in south Seattle that is booming with new development. One long-time resident remarked in the local Seattle Magazine that "businesses are moving here, the community is growing, there is a large amount of new construction, and bike paths have been developed." This development has brought in new residents and it's become a great place for young families – nearly 20% of households here have children.

While Seattle city government defines Beacon Hill as consisting of north, mid- and south Beacon Hill plus Holly Park, locals refer to the area as just North and South Beacon Hill.

THINGS TO DO
Seward Park (4.5 miles away) – boasts 300 acres of beautiful forest land on a peninsula that juts out into Lake Washington. It is home to eagles' nests, old growth forest, a 2.4-mile bike and walking path, an amphitheater, a native plant garden, an art studio, miles of hiking trails, shoreline, beaches, boat launch and more

name: Wren's Nest
description:
Set in the vibrant Seattle neighborhood of South Park, this modern open design studio is ready for you to enjoy. Just 15 minutes by car/30 minutes by public transit to downtown Seattle, it's the right mix of city living from the comfort of a historic riverside neighborhood. Enjoy the Duwamish river parks, local restaurants, bars & coffee shop a minute's walk from your door. Spend more time enjoying your trip as South Park is the closest Seattle neighborhood to Seatac airport. Bon voyage!

The space
This bright and airy studio sits high off the ground, providing peaceful views of the surrounding tree canopy. From the deck and through the many windows you can admire Magnolias, Italian fig trees and a thirty foot Cyprus by the bedside window.

The welcoming space is furnished with all new appliances, a full size microwave, oven with glass stovetop & a styling black refrigerator/freezer. The kitchen also features a porcelain farm sink and the cupboards ar
neighborhood_overview: South Park is a vibrant mix of historic river/drawbridge/multi cultural/arts district. South Park is the only Seattle neighborhood directly on the Duwamish River. These fertile grounds are where the very roots for Pike's Place market began as the famers that supplied Pike's Place Market farmed this area. This is also traditional land of the Duwamish People. Our neighborhood boosts not one but three marinas and three parks directly on the Duwamish river.  We are close to downtown (15 minutes by car) and 10 minutes from the airport.  Restaurants and library are two blocks away in either direction. Being close to the airport you can often see and hear airplanes overhead. We are 2.2 miles from the Boeing Museum of Flight a highly recommended adventure into the history of local and international aviation.
host_about:
Hello, first of all we are very excited to host you in our brand new airbnb. My wife and I met here in the South Park neighborhood where we have both lived since 2003. It really is a secret Seattle neighborhood that we are happy to share with you. 
Our family owns a small pizza shop in Seattle's historic Chinatown/International district. We've been open for 11 years and enjoy meeting people from all over the world that come to visit our beautiful city. We also have a small culinary salt business with fresh roasted salts made in small batches we are happy to share with you.
We can't wait to provide you with a little taste of the vibrant city we love. Our home is full of life, with two children, three friendly chickens in the backyard coup, a cat named Sophie who stays on the property and one a tuxedo cat who has many friends throughout the neighborhood. A young dog named Clay finishes out our troop.
Thanks for trusting us with your upcoming stay. We will do our best to make you feel comfortable. 
Cheers!

We invite you to experience a space curated for every need. For a slow morning with coffee on the balcony overlooking Lake Union, a short family walk to Capitol Hill for lunch, or a sunset view of the Space Needle - look no further than The Lakeview Flat.

Our apartment is steps away from Seattle's vibrant shops and restaurants (Fremont, Eastlake, Capitol Hill, and South Lake Union). A dedicated parking spot enables you to drive or use public transportation.

We look forward to your stay.

The space
Our space is a 1,375 square foot apartment that includes 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, in unit washer/dryer, and a complete kitchen that is provisioned with everything needed to prepare a home-cooked meal.

King-sized bed in the primary bedroom, a queen-sized bed in the 2nd bedroom, and a high-end pullout sofa in the living room.

There is also dedicated workspace, which includes internet access with gigabit speed.

Two

name: Condo in Historic Building - Quirky & Quaint
description:

The apartments are open plan style with historical touches such as a traditional telephone but come with great modern amenities such as a flat-screen smart TV, great WiFi, a fully equipped kitchen, and a comfy bed with lots of pillows and linens.

It’s the little things that make a difference, especially when you’re away from home, We go above and beyond to guarantee our place provides guests with all the comforts of home, plus the small luxuries that will make your stay memorable. We ensure that your furnished apartment delivers everything you need to stay different—and live better.

You'll benefit from a recently upgraded kitchen with everything you need.

Cozy private bedroom and bathroom studio in a newly-constructed Seattle modern townhome located in the safe and beautiful neighborhood of Magnolia. This sleek guest suite offers a contemporary design, chic furniture, a spa-style bathroom with heated floors, and thoughtful touches that deliver luxurious comfort for a truly relaxing stay. This work-friendly suite is also conveniently located 5mins from Interbay and 15mins from downtown Seattle, perfect for restful nights while working remotely.

The space
The bedroom and bathroom are located in a brand-new townhouse. The suite is located below the host's living quarters, and is self contained with its own private entrance and space. This home also features a dedicated workspace and plenty of closet space, perfect for remote work. Radiant heating and heated bathroom floors maintain comfortable temperatures even in the winter months.

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy convenient access to many of Seattle’s popular destinations while experiencing the secluded, island-like feel of Magnolia. In 5 minutes, you can be at the base of the Space Needle, watching the fish fly at Pike Place Market, having brunch in Magnolia Village, or experiencing exquisite meals at Palisade. In 10 minutes, you can be in front of the Great Wheel, taking in spectacular views at Kerry Park, catching views of the Fremont Troll, strolling along the beach at Discovery Park, or walking up to the gates of Woodland Park Zoo. Steps away is Ella Bailey Park, just 2 blocks away, offering sweeping views of the skyline, tons of lawn space for pups to run, and play structures for little ones to have fun on.

neighborhood_overview:
Magnolia is a quiet, upscale residential community only 7 minutes from downtown Seattle.

Discovery Park - the largest in Seattle - is just 3 blocks away! Miles of hiking trails with beach and lighthouse access as well as beautiful views of Puget Sound and the Olympic Mountains. There are also public tennis and pickle ball courts and a large playground. Two visitor centers including a Native American interpretive center and gift shop. A great place to jog, walk, or wander all year long!

Magnolia Village offers a large variety of Restaurants and shops - and a community center with indoor basketball, outdoor tennis and pickle ball courts, and a large playground.

Seasonal attractions include a farmer’s market (Saturdays from 10am to 2pm; May through October) and Pop Mounger pool. (Summer Months only).

host_about:
Hi, I am Haritha and nice e-meeting you.

Though I host guests on a short term basis too, my units are also sought after by medium term renters like traveling nurses and traveling professionals.

I am particular about providing quality items and furnishings to my guests in order  for them to have a nice comfortable stay at my place. Most of my furniture is made of solid wood or marble, Sony TVs in each bedroom, lamps are UL listed, beds made of solid wood, plush mattresses with protectors, hotel quality bedsheets, luxury towels, Corelle dinnerware, Rubbermaid Brilliance containers and so on.

A note about my superhost status and not many reviews:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Though I show up as superhost, you will notice that I don't have many reviews on Airbnb.  This is a side effect of the longer renting duration of my units and not all bookings happening through Airbnb.

I get a chance of 2-3 reviews maximum in a year. And not all of the bookings come through Airbnb too, so they can’t provide review on the Airbnb website. Many happen through furnishedfinder and FB groups for travel nurses and professionals as well.

Many of my guests seem to like my place after they move-in and many extend their stay.
Many of them don’t take out time and give reviews (or) they give reviews on FB groups that don't show up on Airbnb.

neighborhood_overview: Historic houses sprinkled with luxury new builds make up the community.
host_about:
Welcome to our cozy and stylish loft style home! We're Dan, Andy, Ken and we're thrilled to host you during your stay in Seattle.

Our house is located in the heart of the city, just minutes away from the best restaurants, bars, and attractions. It's the perfect home base for exploring all that Seattle has to offer.

The property itself is bright and airy, with plenty of natural light and comfortable furnishings. We've put a lot of thought into the design, and we hope you'll love the stylish decor as much as we do.

You'll have everything you need for a comfortable stay, including a fully equipped kitchen, high-speed WiFi, and a cozy living room with a smart TV. The bedrooms feature plush queen-sized beds and plenty of closet space for your belongings.

We're always here to help with any questions or recommendations you may need during your stay. We love sharing our favorite local spots with our guests, so don't hesitate to ask!

We look forward to hosting you and making your stay in Seattle unforgettable. Book now to secure your stay!

name: The Greek Room - 8 min to Downtown by Light Rail
description:
This eight bedroom shared house is located in the University District. The UD is home to some of the best coffee shops, movie theaters, bookshops, and ethnic restaurants in Seattle.
Your private room is spacious, clean, and comfortable. The house is only a few blocks away from the University, and 10 minutes drive to Downtown, by car or Uber.
Street parking is the main option for guests.
The host does not live on site and room keys are available by request for a fee.

The space
The bathroom is downstairs on the basement level. Take the hallway to the right of the staircase. Follow the stairs to the left away from the kitchen.
The bathroom is at the foot of the stairs. The light switch is on the outside of the door on the left-hand side.
There are 3 rooms that share this bathroom. Please limit time to 15-20min to respect the other house guests. Remember to turn off any lights you may turn on.
There is also another bathroom upstairs.
neighborhood_overview:
The University District neighborhood is amazing. Alive with different types of people throughout the year. A multitude of restaurants, an incredible year round farmers market (every Sunday,) plus local shops, and easy proximity to downtown Seattle and other popular local neighborhoods. Super easy public transportation in and out of the area makes the UD a prime location.

The University District is a very active neighborhood with a lot of restaurants and cafes. Our neighbors are comprised mostly of students and sometimes they will throw a party on the weekend. But they are very friendly and they will be happy to invite you to join them or turn the volume down if you ask them so.
host_about: Welcome to Seattle! I am a young photographer and part time Airbnb host passionate about travel, food and the outdoors. I hope you have a great stay here in the Emerald City!

name: The Boho Room in the Central District
description:
This is a private room in my 7 bedroom house in Seattle's historic Central District.
We are just a 5 min drive east of downtown and just South of the hip and artistic Capitol Hill neighborhood.
This is a great, clean and quiet location to rest your head at night and meet other travelers also exploring Seattle.
Two buses a couple of blocks away take you to Downtown and Capitol Hill in 10 minutes.

The space
This is a private room with all the essentials in a shared house with other travelers sharing the space.

name: Wallingford Fresh - Garden level 1 BR apartment
description:
Asian-inspired garden-level apartment in Wallingford neighborhood - centrally located, quietly residential. Make a meal in your fully equipped kitchen, or walk to local restaurants, shops, transit, and parks. Perfect for longer term stays. Your peace in the city.

The space
This lovely space is a fully equipped "mother-in-law" apartment in the remodeled basement of our family home. It includes a full-sized kitchen, bedroom with closets, private bath with shower, living room with TV/stereo, and dining area. Wi-fi, towels, linens, soaps and toiletries are provided. Laundry can be shared with prior arrangement. We live upstairs, so normal activities of daily life may be audible from the guest space, but we keep it minimal and maintain quiet hours from 10 pm to 7 am.

Guest access
Private entrance. Enter through side gate and step down to your own private entrance. Guests are welcome to enjoy the sunny garden patio in the private backyard.
neighborhood_overview: Located just 2 blocks from the heart of the Wallingford neighborhood's main street, close to coffee shops, restaurants and services. We are a short 15-minute walk from Greenlake, the Burke-Gilman trail and Gasworks Park, with easy access to downtown, the University district, Fremont and Ballard neighborhoods. I-5, I-99 and bus routes easily accessible.

name: A-Center of Capital Hill- 3
description:
Heart of Capitol Hill, come enjoy the characters and the history of our neighborhood: original historic landmark home to restaurateur and neighborhood activist Mario. Your stay here helps us preserve our history. The parks, clubs, bars, galleries, boutiques and coffeehouses, is right outside your door. Our house is a Walker's Paradise with highest walking score in the city, next to the capital hill light rail station. Steps away there are restaurants, grocery stores, retail shops, recreational

The space
You will have a private secured room, 2 full size bed (1 is foldable futon/couch). Kitchen and bath are community space (3 occupants at max capacity), regularly attended by our diligent cleaning crew.

Guest access
All common space including the backyard

Other things to note
We are certieid by Airbnb Enhanced Clean (https://news.airbnb.com/introducing-airbnb-enhanced-clean/).
We ask our guests to please refill
neighborhood_overview:
Capital Hill is undeniably the Seattle's current coolest 'hood. It’s home to the city’s musicians and artists, counterculture mavens, and (for better or worse) flocks of yuppies attracted to the neighborhood’s unique spirit -- especially the dozens of bars, restaurants, music venues, and theaters that dot its landscape.

If you’re visiting Capitol Hill for the first time, it can be overwhelming, because there is so much to do. Capitol Hill is one of Seattle’s most popular neighborhoods. A hotspot of nightlife and restaurants, and the center of Seattle’s vibrant variety of independent shops, including one of the city’s largest bookstores. Just a few blocks north of the retail area, residents can find houses ranging from modest to grand. Capitol Hill has easy access to downtown as well as points north and south thanks to a light rail station in the heart of the neighborhood. For something quieter, residents can visit Cal Anderson Park, Volunteer Park, or one of the many area g
host_about:
Welcome to our community!  We have a team managing your stay.  We love our guests.

When I first arrived in the Pacific Northwest, it felt like coming home. My husband is a 5th generation Seattleite.  I knew this was the place for my kids to grow and thrive.  For almost 20 years I helped people find their homes here, helping my neighbors and my community preserving the history of their older homes.  

I have a genuine interest in houses, architecture, & construction and an interest to show you the beauty of our area.
 
Since 2000, I managed thousands of furnished rental homes,  If you live here now and want a change, please let us know.
 
This is not just one of the areas I represent.  This is my home.  This is my community.

name: A-Lake Union One Br Apt- Sleep 4
description:
This fun mother in law apartment in Seattle is the perfect quaint getaway only minutes from all the excitement Seattle has to offer, and walking distance to beautiful Lake Union. Make yourself at home- enjoy a fully stocked kitchen, TV, and Wifi! Just minutes to downtown attractions, craft breweries, trendy eateries, indie shops.
We are certified by Airbnb Enhanced Clean. We ask our guests to please refill your own essentials, after the initial supplies are consumed.

The space
Fun in Seattle awaits you in this awesome 1-bedroom 1-bath vacation rental apartment! With enough space to sleep up to 4, this is one of the best locations in Seattle that won't break the bank! You’ll love our place because of the comfy bed and futons, tranquil urban ambiance, and convenience to everything Seattle has to offer. View of space needle, downtown, Lake Union, and Queen Ann. In the heart of Eastlake, surrounded by incredible restaurants, stores and spas, 1 block from Lake U
neighborhood_overview: With Amazon worldwide headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union.  There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

The space
This is one of the best locations in Seattle. You’ll love our place because of the comfy, tranquil urban ambiance, and convenience to everything Seattle has to offer. neighborhood_overview:
Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park. The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water. Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

Right on Greenlake, you will love this neighborhood: pedestrian friendly, family recreation, the zoo, library, trendy restaurants, cafes, tennis courts, fowing facilities, several bus routes. Easy access to I-5, HW 99. 1.5 miles to Downtown Seattle, 3 miles to Amazon headquarters, 4 miles to Starbucks headquarters/11 miles to Microsoft.

There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

neighborhood_overview: With Amazon worldwide headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union. neighborhood_overview:
Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park. The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water. Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

Right on Greenlake, you will love this neighborhood: pedestrian friendly, family recreation, the zoo, library, trendy restaurants, cafes, tennis courts, fowing facilities, several bus routes. Easy access to I-5, HW 99. 1.5 miles to Downtown Seattle, 3 miles to Amazon headquarters, 4 miles to Starbucks headquarters/11 miles to Microsoft. New wood floor just put in 2 weeks ago.

neighborhood_overview:
Capital Hill is undeniably the Seattle's current coolest 'hood. It’s home to the city’s musicians and artists, counterculture mavens, and (for better or worse) flocks of yuppies attracted to the neighborhood’s unique spirit -- especially the dozens of bars, restaurants, music venues, and theaters that dot its landscape.

If you’re visiting Capitol Hill for the first time, it can be overwhelming, because there is so much to do. Capitol Hill is one of Seattle’s most popular neighborhoods. A hotspot of nightlife and restaurants, and the center of Seattle’s vibrant variety of independent shops, including one of the city’s largest bookstores. neighborhood_overview: With Amazon headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union.  There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

neighborhood_overview:
Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park. The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water. Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

Right on Greenlake, you will love this neighborhood: pedestrian friendly, family recreation, the zoo, library, trendy restaurants, cafes, tennis courts, fowing facilities, several bus routes. Easy access to I-5, HW 99. 1.5 miles to Downtown Seattle, 3 miles to Amazon headquarters, 4 miles to Starbucks headquarters/11 miles to Microsoft.

neighborhood_overview:
Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park. The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water. Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

Right on Greenlake, you will love this neighborhood: pedestrian friendly, family recreation, the zoo, library, trendy restaurants, cafes, tennis courts, fowing facilities, several bus routes. Easy access to I-5, HW 99. 1.5 miles to Downtown Seattle, 3 miles to Amazon headquarters, 4 miles to Starbucks headquarters/11 miles to Microsoft.

host_about:
Hi, We are Joe and Lolo!

We love to travel and are drawn to vacation homes as there is so much opportunity to spend time together and make memories, whether grilling together on the deck, or snuggling up to a movie after a day of exploring the great outdoors.
Still, most homes (even expensive ones) were missing the "Luxury" factor and the concierge services we used to enjoy at hotels. So, we brought that element into our collection of vacation homes.
We curate the entire experience, bringing together the best team of support staff, designers, and local talent. From excursions and local tours, to private chefs and amenities usually only found in five star resorts, our guests can relax and enjoy not only a gorgeous home with all the comforts, but also an experience to remember without the hassles.
In addition to our own properties, we are helping homeowners from across the country manage their investment properties and vacation homes . We are not your ordinary property manager. We are obsessed with improving the guest experience, which translates to a superior experience and performance for property owners.

The space
The Wallingford Oasis is an open and airy unit sitting on top of an old, now closed Seattle restaurant. You enter the gate, walk down to the back of the building, and climb a set of stairs to arrive at the front door. Upon entering, you will find yourself in the dining area, with the kitchen to the right. To the left you'll find a place to hang your coat and store your shoes. neighborhood_overview:
Wallingford is a laid back neighborhood in the northwest region of Seattle popular with singles and, given its proximity to the University of Washington, students.

In the center of the neighborhood is its main commercial thoroughfare, 45th Street, which is home to tons of restaurants and shops. An influx of well-known chefs and trendy restaurants has raised the bar for dining here.

On Wallingford's south edge Gas Works Park has plenty of green rolling hills for a lazy weekend picnic by the water and the remnants of – no surprise given the park's name – an old gasification plant, some of which has been configured into a children's play area (yes, it's safe).

Wallingford is bordered on the north by Green Lake, on the east by University District, on the south by Lake Union, and on the west by Fremont and Phinney Ridge.

Fremont is a neighborhood with a little of everything that makes Seattle awesome, like outdoorsy pursuits, proximity to the water, foodie delights, unique shopping, interesting architecture, and a bit of quirk. Theo Chocolate is a Seattle company worth a visit. The shop is all about fair trade organic chocolate in every variety under the rainbow.
